4. Semaphore-Specific Integration Points
Semaphore itself exports triples in standard formats (Turtle, N-Triples, RDF/XML, SKOS). From there you can index them via:

SPARQL Update / LOAD into any SPARQL 1.1–compliant store (GraphDB, Stardog, Virtuoso, Jena Fuseki)
REST APIs — most triplestores accept bulk RDF uploads via HTTP
ETL pipelines using tools like Apache NiFi, Talend, or RML Mapper for automated triple extraction and loading
AllegroGraph has a native Semaphore connector documented on their platform



 2. Ontology / Triple Ingestion & Transformation Tools
These help convert, map, or pipe triples into a triplestore:

SemTK (Semantics Toolkit) — An open-source toolkit that allows users to convert CSV data into RDF triples and ingest them into a triple store, and also provides REST APIs for all functionality including data ingestion and queries. https://arxiv.org/pdf/1710.11531
Ontop / Ontopic Studio — Supports reasoning, RDF generation, SPARQL endpoints, and RDB-to-RDF conversion, directly usable from Java. https://www.w3.org/RDF/
J2RM — A tool to process mappings from JSON data to RDF triples guided by an OWL2 ontology structure. https://github.com/semantalytics/awesome-semantic-web
ROBOT — A widely used ontology processing tool that can generate diffs, transform, and export ontology content in OWL/OBO formats for downstream ingestion.

